egistered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 6:10:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Confirmation on Shroud of Nature info-</span><hr size=1> ok, Tunnel north of archs is safe spot right? 1 wanderer in tunnel? then you can pull the dude at tent south of tunnel and around the archs without aggroing others? do they not assist or what? I am level 47 BTW.<br>
<br>
Dyladru Stormcaller<br>
47th Lvl Halfling Druid<br>
Fallen Serripham<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kloef>Kloef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 7:17:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shroud of Nature</span><hr size=1> I have been in there and soloed the Warder, at 49, you can do it just the same.<br>
<br>
The spawns near the arches and the tent can be single pulled, trust me.<br>
<br>
I found out on my own by taking a chance, nothing ventured nothing gained I always say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/16/01 6:53:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shroud of Nature</span><hr size=1> Just keep in mind that if anything is close enough to heal, it will without actually joining in on the fight.  Sometimes you have to try to pull to a different spot initially for the break or take the healer(s) out first.<br>
<br>
 <p>-Galipure Stormdancer<BR>Sun Clan of Warriors<BR>Solusek Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kloef>Kloef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/16/01 1:19:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solo Warder</span><hr size=1> Its true you do have to worry about the roaming healers, however, as I have stated in other posts, it depends on where you pull too. If you are in the tunnel just past the arches you only have to worry about one roamer, Root/DOT him till dead, then pull the surrounding gobs (3), all single, remember to keep track of the respawn time of the roamer ( 20 mins ).<br>
<br>
Thats it, thats how I have gotten 2 shrouds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kloef>Kloef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/16/01 1:24:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solo Warder</span><hr size=1> Oh and another thing, lol, I love this topic.<br>
<br>
If your out of mana and the roamer is about to pop, you can move to the tent area to med, just break the spawn properly.<br>
<br>
With 4 possible PH the warder will eventually pop, like all camps be patient. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyladrustormcaller>Dyladru Stormcaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 3:16:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo Warder</span><hr size=1> Well i went last night, was really only able to control 2 or 3 spawns due to the damn cleric class goblins healin themselves so much, but i was there for 7 hours, 3 hours with a friend and we had every single spawn around the arch whooped and were pullin extras from the city. 7 hours there, one warder, no shroud. Heh i guess i really am jynxed when it comes to spawns.<br>
<br>
Dyladru Stormcaller<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uneek11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neek11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 4:52:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo Warder</span><hr size=1> Dyladru...<br>
<br>
Don't feel bad...I spent about 15 hours there solo or paired with a tank before I got my shroud on about my 14th warder...Grrrrrrr <p>Neek Neekerbeekers<BR>
Halfling Wanderer of the 54th Leaf<BR>Seekers of Divinity<BR>Rallos Zek
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvehn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vehn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 8:19:17 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Solo Warder</span><hr size=1> Hmm.. by &quot;just past the arches&quot; do you mean south of them in the tunnel just east of the tent?  Because I had 3 roamers in a row there the other day and almost bit it.. where EXACTLY is the safest spot to pull to? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyladrustormcaller>Dyladru Stormcaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 11:25:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Confirmation on Shroud of Nature info-</span><hr size=1> i am in the tunnel north of the arches <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvehn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vehn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 1:11:26 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Confirmation on Shroud of Nature info-</span><hr size=1> Gonna try to PL/camp a shroud with a 38 rogue and a 51 druid tonight, we'll see ^^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukanwe2k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kanwe2k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/01 8:48:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Confirmation on Shroud of Nature info-</span><hr size=1> Looking at this map <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?id=384245">www.everlore.com/ShowScre...?id=384245</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> , is the best area to camp for the shroud in the Gob city or the &quot;dining room&quot;.  I've seen the dining room labled differently on different maps.<br>
<br>
Thanx<br>
Kan<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujhovallww.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JhovallWW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/01 1:59:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Confirmation on Shroud of Nature info-</span><hr size=1> The tunnel north of the arches is, in fact, the safest place to pull to. Only one gobbie will spawn in the tunnel. Any of the goblins in the area can spawn a warder (there's about 15 of them). At 49 I was only able to take 6 or 7 spawns per 20 minute cycle. This is with ES gear. Just root/dot the warrior types and nuke the casters with starfire. At 49, I could pull a goblin from past the arches without pulling any extras. I've actually seen a 50 necro easily take all the spawns with time to spare. Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
Jhovall Winterwolf<br>
51 Wanderer<br>
The Nameless<br>
<br>
